  "description": "Domesticated ducks (Anas platyrhynchos domesticus, Cairina moschata) raised for eggs, meat, and pest control. Khaki Campbell ducks produce 250-340 eggs per year, exceeding most chicken breeds. Ducks are superior foragers of slugs, snails, and aquatic plants, and are more disease-resistant than chickens.",
